## Conjecture (CPRR)
1. Wiring telemetry into the REPL hot path will not measurably
   degrade chat latency on the LAN. POST round trip to nexus is
   ~10-20ms vs the multi-second LLM turn.
2. The session_id label is high-cardinality but bounded (one new
   value per /exit). Acceptable for Prometheus retention.
3. The active.time/user counter is wall-clock time on readline,
   which conflates \"thinking\" with \"AFK\". Not ideal but matches
   the Claude Code dashboard's CLI vs User panel semantics.
4. tool_decision should fire on the reject path even though no
   real reject path exists in YOLO mode. Future-proofing for
   when permission gates ship.

