## Refutation / known limits
- The follow-up non-streaming chat inside the streaming tool-call
  branch (when handle-chat dispatches to ollama-chat) does NOT
  flush telemetry. The tool_decision counter from execute-tool
  sits in memory until the NEXT user turn (or /exit). We hit this
  during the smoke test and worked around by /exit'ing. Filed in
  release notes as a follow-up.
- The active.time CLI counter is wrapped around the WHOLE
  repl-eval call including command parsing and tool dispatch. If
  the user issues a /command (no LLM call), the time is still
  attributed to type=cli. Probably acceptable but worth noting.
- 'model-not-found friendly catch only handles the symbol thrown
  by ollama.scm. Other error paths in the chat code still fall
  through to the generic format printer. Fine for now; the
  telemetry-flush failure path is silent on purpose.
- Late-bound module-ref for *session* is a workaround for a Guile
  module binding race. The right long-term fix is a session-id
  accessor function exported from (sage session) so callers don't
  need to module-ref a mutable variable.

